join Teodora right
Teodora: Jose, my son. You have finally returned home.
join Rizal left
Rizal: Mother, I missed our home more than words can say.
leave Teodora
join Paciano center
Paciano: Europe has changed you.
Rizal: It has opened my eyes to what our country could become.
leave Rizal
leave Paciano
join Villagers center
Villagers: Doctor Rizal, they say you studied in Europe.
join Rizal left
Rizal: Yes. If I can help heal our people, then my journey was worth it.
Villagers: My eyesight has been troubling me.
Rizal: Sit down. Let me examine your eyes.
leave Villagers
join dominicanfriars center
\dominicanfriars: Señor Rizal, we have heard of your book.
Rizal: It is only a story that reflects reality.
\dominicanfriars: Stories like that can create dangerous ideas.
Rizal: Truth should not be feared.
\dominicanfriars: You would be wise to remember who governs this colony.
leave dominicanfriars
join Paciano center
Paciano: Jose, they are watching you.
Rizal: I expected as much. But the truth cannot remain hidden forever.